# SOCIAL NETWORK EXPLORER REPORT

## 1. Aim

To design and implement a simplified Social Network Explorer using:
- Hashing
- Graphs
- BFS
- DFS
- Sorting

---

## 2. Features Implemented

### Profile Management
- Add user
- Get profile
- Update profile

### Social Network Graph
- Add friendships
- Remove friendships
- Display friends list

### BFS
Used to find shortest path between users.

### DFS
Used to explore friends-of-friends up to a certain depth.

### Friend Recommendation
Suggested users based on common interests.

---

## 3. Data Structures Used

| Feature | Data Structure |
|---------|----------------|
| Profiles | Dictionary (Hashing) |
| Network | Graph Adjacency List |
| BFS | Queue |
| DFS | Recursion + Set |
| Recommendation | Sorting + Hashing |

---

## 4. Complexity Analysis

### BFS
Time Complexity: O(V + E)

### DFS
Time Complexity: O(V + E)

### Hash Table Operations
Average Complexity: O(1)

### Sorting Recommendations
Time Complexity: O(n log n)

---

## 5. Design Decisions

- Dictionary was used for fast profile lookup.
- Graph adjacency list was used for efficient connections.
- BFS was selected for shortest path discovery.
- DFS was used for depth-based exploration.

---

## 6. Conclusion

The Social Network Explorer successfully demonstrated:
- Profile management
- Social graph connections
- BFS shortest path
- DFS exploration
- Friend recommendation system

All required capstone objectives were completed successfully.